-- Endpoint Security Controls --

Endpoint Security Controls:

â€¢ Antivirus / Antimalware
  â†’ Scans files and activities
  â†’ Matches patterns and signatures
â€¢ Endpoint Detection and Response (EDR)
  â†’ Real-time monitoring and response
  â†’ Agent-based deployment
  â†’ Monitors process, file, registry, and network activity
â€¢ Extended Detection and Response (XDR)
  â†’ Integration of multiple security controls and telemetry
  â†’ Runbooks and automated response to routine threats
â€¢ Data Loss Prevention (DLP)
  â†’ Protects sensitive data at rest, transit, and in processing
  â†’ Access controls, data masking, and prevention
â€¢ User and Entity Behavior Analytics (UBA)
  â†’ Monitors user behavior patterns
  â†’ Detects deviations from historic and contextual baselines
  â†’ Identifies insider threats, account compromise, and data exfiltration
â€¢ HIDS / HIPS
  â†’ HIDS: Host-based Intrusion Detection System
  â†’ HIPS: Host-based Intrusion Prevention System
â€¢ Host-based Firewall
  â†’ Controls incoming and outgoing traffic on a host

Endpoint Security Monitoring

â€¢ Process Execution
  â†’ Monitoring running processes
  â†’ Executable files, PIDs, and command-line arguments
  â†’ Parent-child process hierarchy
â€¢ File System Changes
  â†’ Creation, modification, and deletion
  â†’ File Integrity Monitoring (FIM)
â€¢ Network Connections
  â†’ Traffic and connections initiated from the endpoint
  â†’ Associated processes and executables
â€¢ Registry Modifications
  â†’ Monitor registry keys and values
  â†’ Detect backdoors, persistence, and detection evasion



-- Windows Network Analysis --

ğŸ”§ CMD Network Commands

net share â†’ View local shares
net share Exfil=C:\Users\admin\Downloads\exfil â†’ Create a share named â€œExfilâ€ pointing to a folder (mount for sharing)
net use X: \127.0.0.1\Exfil â†’ Map network share Exfil to drive X:
net use â†’ Show mapped drives and active sessions
net view â†’ List computers and visible shares on the network
net view \127.0.0.1\ â†’ View shares on the local machine (by IP)
net view \HOSTNAME â†’ View shares on a specific host
net share \127.0.0.1\ â†’ Show local shares via IP path
net session â†’ Show active SMB sessions on this machine


ğŸŒ Network Statistics

netstat -anob â†’ Show all active connections with owning process/EXE
netstat -anob [ESTABLISHED] â†’ Show only established connections
netstat -e â†’ Display Ethernet statistics
netstat -nr â†’ Show routing table (numeric mode)
netstat -S â†’ Display per-protocol statistics
netstat -vb â†’ Show verbose info including the executable (admin required)


ğŸ“¡ IP / ARP / Routing

ipconfig /all â†’ Show detailed adapter configuration
arp -a â†’ View ARP cache (IP-to-MAC mappings)
route print â†’ Display system routing table
nbtstat -n â†’ Show local NetBIOS name table
nbtstat -A [IP] â†’ Display remote NetBIOS information


âš¡ PowerShell Network Commands

Get-NetAdapter â†’ View network interface card info
Get-NetIPAddress â†’ Display IPv4 and IPv6 configuration
Get-NetIPConfiguration â†’ Show full IP configuration
Get-NetRoute â†’ Display routing table

Get-NetTCPConnection â†’ Show active TCP connections (netstat equivalent)
Get-NetUDPEndpoint â†’ Display active UDP ports

Get-SmbShare â†’ View SMB shared folders
Get-SmbSession â†’ Show active SMB sessions
Get-SmbMapping â†’ Display mapped network drives
New-SmbShare -Name X -Path C:\ â†’ Create a new SMB share

Resolve-DnsName google.com â†’ Perform DNS lookup (like nslookup)
Test-Connection google.com â†’ Ping alternative using PowerShell
Test-NetConnection -Port 80 â†’ Test port connectivity

Get-NetFirewallRule â†’ View firewall rules
Get-NetFirewallProfile â†’ Check firewall status


ğŸ§  WMI-Based Network Enumeration

Get-WmiObject Win32_NetworkAdapterConfiguration â†’ Show NICs with IPs, MACs, and gateways
Get-WmiObject Win32_NetworkAdapter â†’ Display all network adapters
Get-WmiObject Win32_Share â†’ List all network shares
Get-WmiObject Win32_ServerConnection â†’ Show current network sessions
Get-WmiObject Win32_NetworkConnection â†’ View mapped network drives


ğŸ’¡ Other Useful Utilities

whoami /groups â†’ Show user group memberships
nltest /dclist:domain â†’ List domain controllers
net config workstation â†’ Show computer name and joined domain
net time \server â†’ Test time synchronization with a server
nslookup â†’ Perform DNS lookup
ping â†’ Test reachability and latency
tracert â†’ Trace network route to a host
pathping â†’ Combined ping + traceroute diagnostics


